======================================================================
PART 2: The (c3, c5, c7) decomposition at n=7
======================================================================

  At n=7, a1 = c3 + c5 + c7.
  c3 = number of cyclic triples (3-cycles)
  c5 = number of directed 5-cycles
  c7 = 0 or 1 (existence of directed Hamiltonian cycle)

  For H=21, need a1 + 2*a2 = 10.
  a2 = disjoint pairs of 3-cycles.

