======================================================================
PART 3: Why a1=10 at n=7 is trapped
======================================================================

  a1 = c3 + c5 + c7 = 10
  c7 in {0, 1}
  Possible decompositions: (c3, c5, c7) with c3+c5+c7=10

  Score sequence constraint: c3 = 35 - sum C(s_i, 2)
  For c3=10: sum C(s_i, 2) = 25
  For c3=9: sum C(s_i, 2) = 26
  For c3=8: sum C(s_i, 2) = 27

  c3=8: need sum C(s_i,2) = 27
    Score sequence: (0, 3, 3, 3, 4, 4, 4), c3=8
    Score sequence: (1, 1, 3, 4, 4, 4, 4), c3=8
    Score sequence: (1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 4, 5), c3=8
    Score sequence: (2, 2, 2, 2, 3, 5, 5), c3=8
    Score sequence: (2, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3, 6), c3=8

  c3=9: need sum C(s_i,2) = 26
    Score sequence: (1, 2, 2, 4, 4, 4, 4), c3=9
    Score sequence: (1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 4, 5), c3=9
    Score sequence: (2, 2, 2, 2, 4, 4, 5), c3=9

  c3=10: need sum C(s_i,2) = 25
    Score sequence: (1, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4, 4), c3=10
    Score sequence: (1, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 5), c3=10
    Score sequence: (2, 2, 2, 3, 3, 4, 5), c3=10

