======================================================================
PART 5: The RIGID constraint — c3 determines a2 range
======================================================================

  a2=0 requires: every pair of 3-cycles shares a vertex.
  This means the 3-cycles form a CLIQUE in the conflict graph.

  Maximum clique in conflict graph of 3-cycles on 7 vertices:
  A 3-cycle uses 3 of 7 vertices.
  Two 3-cycles conflict iff they share >= 1 vertex.
  Two 3-cycles are DISJOINT only if they share 0 vertices (using 6 of 7).

  For c3 cycles with a2=0: ALL cycles pairwise conflict.
  Max # of pairwise conflicting 3-cycles on 7 vertices:
  If they all share vertex v, up to C(6,2)=15 cycles through v.
  But not all of those need to be 3-cycles in the tournament.

  KEY: if c3=10 and a2=0, all 10 cyclic triples share a common vertex.
  But with 10 triples on 7 vertices, Helly-type argument...

  Frequency of a2=0 by c3:
